## üèÜ Golden Rules (Memorize These)

### Rule 0: RESEARCH FIRST

```
Before writing ANY code:
1. Search npm for packages    ‚Üí "npm [problem] react"
2. Search blogs for solutions ‚Üí "[problem] react 2024 best practice"
3. Check package.json         ‚Üí Already installed?
4. Only then write custom     ‚Üí If nothing found
```

### Rule 1: USE EXISTING PACKAGES

```
Server state    ‚Üí TanStack Query (NOT useState+useEffect)
Forms           ‚Üí react-hook-form + zod (NOT manual state)
UI Components   ‚Üí shadcn/ui CLI (NOT build from scratch)
Toasts          ‚Üí Sonner (NOT custom)
Animations      ‚Üí Framer Motion (NOT CSS keyframes)
Dates           ‚Üí date-fns (NOT custom)
Icons           ‚Üí Lucide React (NOT custom SVG)
```

### Rule 2: FOLLOW THE PATTERN

```
pages/[Feature].tsx              ‚Üí Container (state, API)
components/[feature]/            ‚Üí UI components
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ComponentA.tsx             ‚Üí Single responsibility
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ComponentB.tsx             ‚Üí Single responsibility
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ index.tsx                  ‚Üí Composes all
types/[feature].ts               ‚Üí Types
query-key/[feature].ts           ‚Üí Query keys
```

### Rule 3: COPY > CREATE

```bash
# Find similar pattern
grep -r "useQuery" src/pages/
# Copy and modify
```

### Rule 4: SIMPLE > CLEVER

```typescript
